    <text id="B1136T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Cook asks for a five-day leave of absence to go to Washington, D.C.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau Refugees, Freedmen and <abbr expan="Abandoned Lands"
                        >A.L.</abbr><lb/>Office <abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst Supt.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Sub-District">Sub-Dist</abbr> No. 10 7th <abbr expan="District"
                        >Dist</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Brevet <abbr expan="Brigadier General">Brig Genl</abbr>
                        O. Brown<lb/>A.A.A.G.<lb/>Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> (<orig
                            reg="through">thro'</orig>
                        <abbr expan="Headquarters">H<hi rend="super">d</hi>Qrs</abbr> Seventh <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>)</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-10-18"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 18<hi
                                rend="super">th</hi> 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton Augusta <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr>
                            <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to request "Leave of Absence" for five (5) days to visit
                    Washington D.C. on important private business.</p>

                <p>I have been on duty in the "Bureau" since the 2<hi rend="super">d</hi> of April
                    1866 during which time I have not had a "Leave of Absence."</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obt.</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>Geo. T. Cook.<lb/>1st <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Veterans' Reserve Corps">V.R.C.</abbr> and <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst. Supt.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
